{
  "doc_id": "16561",
  "text": "2,4-dichlorophenoxyacetic acid (2,4-D) is, an environmental contaminant, commonly found in the surface water and groundwater near agriculture fields or golf courses. It is utilized as a systemic herbicide to control many types of broadleaf weeds and as a plantgrowth regulator in agriculture and gardening. 2,4-D has been shown to be successfully mineralized in water by various advanced oxidation processes (AOPs) such as UV/H 2 O 2 [CITATION_1] , TiO 2 /sunlight [CITATION_2] , and sonolysis [CITATION_3] . In addition, the well-known Fenton's reaction (see Eq. (1)) is also found to be improved by UV irradiation in transforming 2,4-D more effectively. ",
